# Markdown Quality Standards

## MANDATORY MARKDOWN FORMATTING RULES

### Headers
- Headers must have blank lines before and after them
- No trailing punctuation in headers (no colons, periods, etc.)
- Use proper header hierarchy (# ## ### ####)

### Lists
- Lists must be surrounded by blank lines
- Use consistent list formatting (all bullets or all numbers)
- Proper indentation for nested lists

### Code Blocks
- Use proper language identifiers for syntax highlighting
- Ensure code blocks are properly closed
- No trailing whitespace in code blocks

### Links and References
- All links must be valid and accessible
- Use descriptive link text
- Check that internal references exist

## LINTING REQUIREMENTS

### Markdownlint Compliance
- MD022: Headers surrounded by blank lines
- MD026: No trailing punctuation in headers
- MD032: Lists surrounded by blank lines
- MD013: Line length limits (100 characters)
- MD040: Fenced code blocks with language
- MD041: First line must be header
- MD033: No inline HTML (use markdown syntax)

### Python Code Quality
- No unused imports (W0611)
- No unused arguments (W0613)
- Proper exception handling with 'from' clause (W0707)
- Snake_case naming conventions (C0103)
- No multiple statements on single line (C0321)
- Proper import order (C0411, C0412)
- No trailing newlines (C0305)

## ENFORCEMENT

### Before Creating Documentation
- Run markdownlint check
- Validate all links and references
- Ensure proper header structure
- Check code examples for syntax errors

### Quality Gates
- No markdownlint errors allowed
- No broken links
- All code examples must be functional
- Proper formatting throughout document

### Auto-Fix Requirements
- Remove trailing whitespace
- Fix header formatting
- Correct list spacing
- Validate and fix links
- Ensure consistent formatting

## DOCUMENTATION STANDARDS

### Structure
- Clear hierarchy with proper headers
- Consistent formatting throughout
- Logical flow and organization
- Complete and accurate information

### Content Quality
- All examples must work
- Links must be current and valid
- No placeholder text or TODOs
- Professional tone and clarity

### Maintenance
- Regular link validation
- Update examples when code changes
- Keep formatting consistent
- Remove outdated information
